# SSH config & the agent

## `~/.ssh/config` — save aliases

```
Host work
    HostName 10.0.0.42
    User alice
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/work_ed25519

Host internal-*
    ProxyJump bastion
```

Now `ssh work` connects with the right key; `ssh internal-db1` **jumps through** bastion. Rules: patterns (globs), **first match wins**, `Host *` sets defaults. Keys: `HostName` · `User` · `Port` · `IdentityFile` · `ProxyJump`.

## `ssh-agent` — unlock the key once

```bash
ssh-add          # add id_ed25519 to the agent
ssh-add -l       # list held keys
```

Passphrase costs you once per session.

## Agent forwarding vs ProxyJump

`ssh -A` lets a server use **your** agent for an onward hop — key never leaves your laptop. ⚠️ But that host can use your key while connected — **not for untrusted servers**. **`ProxyJump` is safer** — tunnels through, no agent access.
